@761 = ~Entropic Weapon~
@762 = ~Entropic Weapon (Evocation)
Level: 6
Range: 0
Duration: 3 rounds/2 levels
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: special
Saving Throw: none

This spell brings up into the hands of the warlord a bubble of wild magic, that he shapes into a weapon he masters. The weapon can not leave his hand for the duration of the spell, unless replaced by another weapon shaped in the same way. This weapon also disrupts everything it hits. It destabilizes the molecules of any armor (natural or not) that it hits and gives a +2 bonus to hitting. It causes a metabolic shock where it hits and inflicts 1D8 +3 additional damage. It also disrupts a magical flow, and any summoned creature struck is immediately sent back (a saving throw vs. spells allows to withstand being sent back, -3 bonus to demons and -6 to any other creature). Finally each hit of the weapon negates a magical protection of the victim (saving throw at -3 to resist), and leaves some wild magic residue that makes automatically fail any spell cast in the following round.

Note: Do not create a two-handed sword or a halberd if you are equipped with a shield; this inconsistency would crash the game. If you want such a weapon, then take under consideration to unequip your shield first.~
